programRuleActions.content: In the description, please include the name of the product, a brief description of the product (2-3 sentences), the date finalized or published, the name of the author(s), and a link to where it can be found (if applicable).

Please capture this event at implementation onset. In the description, please include the name (and number if applicable) of the activity. Also include the implementation period (month, year to month, year) for the activity.
Asking the real question, Marvel OR DC?

In the description, please include the name of the product, a brief description of the product (2-3 sentences), the date finalized or published, the name of the author(s), the name of the other awards that participated in the product development, and a link to where it can be found on the MOMENTUM hub.

Please capture this event at the onset of the partnership. In the description, please include the name of the partner and the purpose of the partnership based on these categories: Knowledge sharing; service providing; standard setting; fund mobilizing; or a combination of two or more of the above. Additionally include the partnership objectives (increasing coverage, equity, quality, efficiency as applicable).

In the description, please include the name of the product, a brief description of the product (2-3 sentences), the date finalized or published, the name of the author(s), and a link to where it can be found on the MOMENTUM hub.
Glory to blue cheese, best cheese in the entire world

In the description, please include the name of the conference or setting for the presentation, the name of the session, the date(s), the name of the presenter(s), the name of the other awards that participated in the session, and a link to where it can be found on the MOMENTUM hub.

Please capture this event at the onset of implementation. In the description, please include the name of the intevention and a short description of its objectives. Also include the name of the global good used if applicable.

Please capture this event at the onset of implementation. In the description, please include the name of the innovation and a short description of its objectives. If relevant, include the theory of change about the potential benefits of the innovation versus existing alternatives, and whether there was demonstrated uptake by the private or public sectorwith information, if available, on whether objective of innovation achieved.

Please capture this event at the completion of the development/implementation of the policy. In the description, please include the name of the policy, a short description of its objectives, its technical (i.e., MNCHN/FP/RH) and cross-cutting areas (i.e., gender, digital, community engagement, social and behavior change, resilience). Additionally select the stage of the policy's process- developed; validated/approved; implemented.
